+# De Giorgi Truncation Is Too Entangled With Closed Pressure Negatives For This Audit
+
+Status: `VERIFIED` local-record screen with `INFERRED` exclusion
+
+De Giorgi truncation is not the right Step-5 architecture for the exact-rewrite
+audit because the repository already treats its main pressure-facing targets as
+effectively exhausted.
+
+The local record says the `beta = 4/3` pressure barrier is sharp across the
+documented routes, records failures for the H^1/BMO, atomic, and interpolation
+variants, and narrows the far-field pressure branch to a negative track. Under
+those prior negatives, choosing De Giorgi again would mainly send the branch
+back toward already-closed pressure work rather than provide a clean new audit
+of exact rewrites.
