+# Stretching Localization Mismatches The Rewrite Audit And Reopens A Killed Branch
+
+Status: `VERIFIED` chain-compatibility screen with `INFERRED` exclusion
+
+`Vorticity stretching localization` is not the right inherited architecture for
+this Step-5 audit.
+
+The mission record already warns that the natural exact-rewrite shortlist
+around Lamb-vector, projected, and vorticity-transport formulations does not
+automatically act on full stretching `S omega . omega`. The geometry route was
+then screened out precisely because local Beltrami or Lamb-vector progress did
+not control the full stretching mechanism under the fixed package.
+
+Using stretching localization here would therefore mismatch the rewrite family
+the chain actually wants to compare and would effectively reopen the killed
+geometry branch under a new label.
+
+Filed from:
